                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate, Ciudad Juárez</hi>
                        </placeName>,<lb/>[<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-outside-research"
                            calendar="gregorian" when="1912-08-20">undated</date>] (<hi
                            rend="italic">Received August 20, 1912—11.45 p.m.</hi>)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Federals occupied Juárez to-day. Civil government to be established to-morrow and
                    railroad traffic resumed. General belief that revolution is ended in State of
                    Chihuahua; refugees will now return to their homes. General rejoicing.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwards.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
